        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 20,
        "value": 1.5,
        "unit": "J/cm²",
        "description": "Fluence range for contaminant removal (e.g., oxides, rust) without ablating Zr substrate; damage threshold ~2.5-4 J/cm² due to high reflectivity. Recommended 1.5 J/cm² for safe surface prep. Conservative for Zr's properties. Source: Ablation threshold studies on Zr (J. Phys. D: Appl. Phys. 2017; similar to Ti alloys)."
